<AltName><entry>SHEFFIELD COMMUNICATION SUPPORT SERVICE</entry>
</AltName>
<Desc><entry>A registered charity that provides support to people whose understanding and expression of language (both written and spoken) has been affected following a stroke.  Two part-time co-ordinators, together with teams of trained volunteers, provide a home visiting service and weekly group sessions where people with aphasia can practice communication skills in a safe and supportive environment.  Also provides group activities including day trips and social events.  Referrals to the service are usually made via a speech and language therapist but self-referrals and referrals from other agencies will be considered (although these are subject to assessment by a speech and language therapist).</entry>
</Desc>
